# =============================================================================
# Supabase Edge Functions — Local Environment (Story 6.10)
# =============================================================================
#
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
# 1. Copy this file: cp supabase/.env.local.example supabase/.env.local
# 2. Run `yarn supabase:start` to spin up local Supabase (Docker required)
# 3. Run `yarn supabase:status` to get local credentials (auto-populated below)
# 4. The values below are the LOCAL defaults from `supabase start` — they work
#    out of the box. Only change them if you customised config.toml ports.
#
# IMPORTANT:
# - .env.local is gitignored (supabase/.gitignore) — never commit real keys
# - These are LOCAL-ONLY values that differ from hosted Supabase
# - For production deployment, keys are auto-injected by Supabase runtime
# =============================================================================

